Program: Outlook
Title: The Prisoner who Took Control
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04c7k7j
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 25 Oct 2016
American Tom Huntley was put in charge of policing other inmates when he was in a Texan jail. In Kosovo's capital city you might find an unusual style icon. We take you to the shop selling clothes inspired by US presidential candidate Hillary Clinton. Sibonakaliso Ndaba is a leading South African choreographer. However, she used to make bombs to use against the regime during apartheid. Barnaby Carder has an unusual passion - for spoons. Barnaby, who goes by Barn the Spoon, spent years travelling around British forests, sleeping between the trees and using the wood to carve his own spoons to sell. (Photo: Tom Huntley, courtesy of Mr. Huntley) Show less